#X text 115 432 values from 0-1, f 8;
#X text 27 152 One could have the modulator oscillator going from -1 to 1 \, but it would double the actual rate to 6 Hz \, because the 0 to -1 range is another cyle. Another detail is that it flips the polarity., f 64;
#X text 27 28 Tremolo is a slow periodic modulation of the amplitude/dynamics. We'll get back to it when talking about Amplitude Modulation in the Synthesis section \, but we can introduce it in here. Below \, we have a sine wave oscillator with a low frequency (at 3 Hz) controlling the amplitude of another sine wave. We rescale the output of the modulating oscillator \, which is -1 to 1 \, to a 0 to 1 range with the [rescale~] object. This is like setting a DC-offset to 0.5!, f 64;
#X obj 686 167 hsl 128 15 0 1 0 0 empty empty empty -2 -8 0 10 #dcdcdc #000000 #000000 0 1;
#X obj 562 352 *~;
#X obj 612 177 nbx 4 14 0.01 20 1 1 empty \$0-LFO empty 0 -8 0 10 #dcdcdc #000000 #000000 3.0494 256;
#X text 732 166 Depth;
#X text 576 176 LFO;
#X obj 612 202 osc~;
#X obj 562 509 out~;
#X obj 782 518 out~;
